                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Hsu Yung-chang</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Hsiung Shih-hui</persName>, at Mukden</hi>
                    <note n="94" xml:id="d505fn94">Copy transmitted to General Marshall by Brig.
                        Gen. Peter T. K. Pee, personal aide to Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-05">5 June
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Executive Headquarters, Peiping, will establish a branch office in Changchun.
                    Pending further instructions, that office shall then start functioning. In the
                    preparatory period you should render every assistance and convenience to the
                    said office.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
